<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":3,"align":"wide","style":{"color":{"text":"#632f91"}}} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-center has-text-color" style="color:#632f91"><strong>Supporting OVW Grantees</strong></h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center">Specific questions about a grant should be directed to your OVW Program specialist, which you can find at <a href="https://www.justice.gov/ovw/contacts-grantees" data-type="URL" data-id="https://www.justice.gov/ovw/contacts-grantees" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">justice.gov/ovw/contacts-grantees</a>. And, for more information about being or becoming an OVW grantee, visit OVWâ€™s website at justice.gov/ovw and listen to OVWâ€™s podcast on how to apply for an OVW grant at <a href="https://www.justice.gov/archives/ovw/podcast/federal-funding-how-apply-ovw-grant" data-type="URL" data-id="https://www.justice.gov/archives/ovw/podcast/federal-funding-how-apply-ovw-grant" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">justice.gov/OVW/podcast/federal-funding-how-apply-OVW-grant</a>.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center">OVWâ€™s community of TA providers, through the TTA Program, provides OVW grantees with the training, expertise, and problem-solving strategies they need to meet the challenges of responding to and addressing sexual assault, domestic violence, dating violence, and stalking. TA2TA serves as a resource to OVW grantees by providing a <a href="/events">calendar</a> of OVW TA provider in-person and online educational events; a <a href="https://ldev.ta2ta.org/directory/" data-type="page" data-id="100">directory of OVW TA providers</a>, projects, and grant programs served; a <a href="https://ldev.ta2ta.org/document-library/" data-type="page" data-id="2156">library of resources</a> developed by OVW TA providers; and a <a href="https://ldev.ta2ta.org/orientations-page" data-type="page" data-id="454">new grantee orientation page</a> for all of OVWâ€™s<br>grant programs.</p>
